.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
Specifies a user\(aqs permissions. For more information, see \fI\%Security and Permissions\fP .
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
\fBRequired Permissions\fP : To use this action, an IAM user must have a Manage permissions level for the stack, or an attached policy that explicitly grants permissions. For more information on user permissions, see \fI\%Managing User Permissions\fP .
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
See also: AWS API Documentation
.sp
See \(aqaws help\(aq for descriptions of global parameters.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
  set\-permission
\-\-stack\-id <value>
\-\-iam\-user\-arn <value>
[\-\-allow\-ssh | \-\-no\-allow\-ssh]
[\-\-allow\-sudo | \-\-no\-allow\-sudo]
[\-\-level <value>]
[\-\-cli\-input\-json | \-\-cli\-input\-yaml]
[\-\-generate\-cli\-skeleton <value>]
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SH OPTIONS
.sp
\fB\-\-stack\-id\fP (string)
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
The stack ID.
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
\fB\-\-iam\-user\-arn\fP (string)
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
The user\(aqs IAM ARN. This can also be a federated user\(aqs ARN.
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
\fB\-\-allow\-ssh\fP | \fB\-\-no\-allow\-ssh\fP (boolean)
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
The user is allowed to use SSH to communicate with the instance.
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
\fB\-\-allow\-sudo\fP | \fB\-\-no\-allow\-sudo\fP (boolean)
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
The user is allowed to use \fBsudo\fP to elevate privileges.
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
\fB\-\-level\fP (string)
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
The user\(aqs permission level, which must be set to one of the following strings. You cannot set your own permissions level.
.INDENT 0.0
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdeny\fP
.IP \(bu 2
\fBshow\fP
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdeploy\fP
.IP \(bu 2
\fBmanage\fP
.IP \(bu 2
\fBiam_only\fP
.UNINDENT
.sp
For more information about the permissions associated with these levels, see \fI\%Managing User Permissions\fP .
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
\fB\-\-cli\-input\-json\fP | \fB\-\-cli\-input\-yaml\fP (string)
Reads arguments from the JSON string provided. The JSON string follows the format provided by \fB\-\-generate\-cli\-skeleton\fP\&. If other arguments are provided on the command line, those values will override the JSON\-provided values. It is not possible to pass arbitrary binary values using a JSON\-provided value as the string will be taken literally. This may not be specified along with \fB\-\-cli\-input\-yaml\fP\&.
.sp
\fB\-\-generate\-cli\-skeleton\fP (string)
Prints a JSON skeleton to standard output without sending an API request. If provided with no value or the value \fBinput\fP, prints a sample input JSON that can be used as an argument for \fB\-\-cli\-input\-json\fP\&. Similarly, if provided \fByaml\-input\fP it will print a sample input YAML that can be used with \fB\-\-cli\-input\-yaml\fP\&. If provided with the value \fBoutput\fP, it validates the command inputs and returns a sample output JSON for that command.
.sp
